"o\", \"t\", \"/\", \"h\", \"t\", \"t\", \"p\", \"s\", \":\", \"/\", \"/\", \"w\", \"w\", \"w\", \".\", \"c\", \"i\", \"s\", \"a\", \".\", \"g\", \"o\", \"v\", \"/\", \"k\", \"n\", \"o\", \"w\", \"n\", \"-\", \"e\", \"x\", \"p\", \"l\", \"o\", \"i\", \"t\", \"e\", \"d\", \"-\", \"v\", \"u\", \"l\", \"n\", \"e\", \"r\", \"a\", \"b\", \"i\", \"l\", \"i\", \"t\", \"i\", \"e\", \"s\", \"-\", \"c\", \"a\", \"t\", \"a\", \"l\", \"o\", \"g\", \"?\", \"f\", \"i\", \"e\", \"l\", \"d\", \"_\", \"c\", \"v\", \"e\", \"=\", \"C\", \"V\", \"E\", \"-\", \"2\", \"0\", \"2\", \"5\", \"-\", \"3\", \"2\", \"4\", \"6\", \"3\"]}\n        ```\n    *   **搜索引擎结果：**\n        ```\n        \n            ## 以下内容是基于此漏洞的搜索结果:\n                [webpage 0 begin] [title] zinzloun/CVE-2025-32463: # CVE-2025-32463 – Sudo EoP Exploit...\n [description] CVE-2025-32463 – Sudo EoP Exploit (PoC) with precompiled library. This repository contains a proof-of-concept (PoC) exploit for CVE-2025-32463, a local privilege escalation vulnerability in sudo discovered by Rich Mirch.\n [link] https://github.com/zinzloun/CVE-2025-32463\n [webpage 0 end]\n[webpage 1 begin] [title] Vulnerability details of CVE-2025-32463\n [description] CVE-2025-32463 POC (Proof-of-concept) exploit CVE-2025-32463 (CVSS 78) is a local privilege escalation vulnerability, introduced in sudo 1914 and present through 1917 The issue allows a local user to run arbitrary commands as root by using sudo’s -R / –chroot option to cause sudo...\n [link] https://vulmon.com/vulnerabilitydetails?qid=CVE-2025-32463\n [webpage 1 end]\n[webpage 2 begin] [title] Critical Sudo Vulnerabilities — CVE-2025–32462 and CVE-2025–32463\n [description] CVE-2025–32462 and CVE-2025–32463 show how subtle flaws in trusted tools can enable root access. With CVE-2025–32463 actively exploited, patch urgently and audit sudoers.\n [link] https://medium.com/@Lakshan_Sameera/critical-sudo-vulnerabilities-cve-2025-32462-and-cve-2025-32463-0ee43d15f942\n [webpage 2 end]\n[webpage 3 begin] [title] [CRITICAL] CVE-2025-32463: Local Privilege Escalation... | VNG Cloud\n [description] [CRITICAL] CVE-2025-32463: Privilege Escalation Vulnerability in Sudo.Due to the severity, ease of exploitation, and the existence of a public exploit, System Administrators are strongly advised to update vulnerable versions of Sudo to version 1.9.17p1 or later as soon as possible.\n [link] https://vngcloud.vn/security-advisories-cve-2025-32463-local-privilege-escalation-to-root\n [webpage 3 end]\n[webpage 4 begin] [title] CVE-2025-32463 : Sudo Vulnerability in Chroot Mode Affects Local...\n [description] CVE-2025-32463. New PoC Exploit Released for Sudo Chroot Privilege Escalation Vulnerability. A critical vulnerability in the widely used Sudo utility has come under scrutiny following the public release of a proof-of-concept exploit...\n [link] https://securityvulnerability.io/vulnerability/CVE-2025-32463\n [webpage 4 end]\n\n            \n        ```\n    *   **漏洞利用代码：**\n        ```\n        /tmp/fc288724cb79448a8820f5962f5f58d4/Dockerfile\n---\n# ----- Dockerfile -----\nFROM ubuntu:24.04\n\nENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive\n\n# 1) Build tool and deps\nRUN apt-get update && \\\n    apt-get install -y build-essential wget libpam0g-dev libselinux1-dev zlib1g-dev \\\n                       pkg-config libssl-dev git ca-certificates && \\\n    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n\n# 2) Build vulnerable sudo(1.9.16p2)\nWORKDIR /opt\nRUN wget https://www.sudo.ws/dist/sudo-1.9.16p2.tar.gz && \\\n    tar xzf sudo-1.9.16p2.tar.gz && \\\n    cd sudo-1.9.16p2 && \\\n    ./configure --disable-gcrypt --prefix=/usr && make && make install\n\n# 3) Make a pwn user\nRUN useradd -m -s /bin/bash pwn\n\n# 4) Copy PoC script\nCOPY sudo-chwoot.sh /home/pwn/sudo-chwoot.sh\nRUN chown pwn:pwn /home/pwn/sudo-chwoot.sh\n\n# 5) Swith to the pwn user\nUSER pwn\nWORKDIR /home/pwn\n\n# 6) Run shell\nCMD [\"/bin/bash\"]\n\n\n---\n/tmp/fc288724cb79448a8820f5962f5f58d4/LICENSE\n---\nMIT License\n\nC